<LegalLayout
  locale="en"
  eyebrow="Sales Terms"
  title="Sales terms — partner clubs"
  description="Scluba sales terms for partner golf clubs — subscription, pricing, payment, term, service level, termination, liability."
  altPathname="/legal/cgv/"
  updated="2026-05-06"
>
  <p class="legal-callout">
    <strong>Pilot phase — first month free</strong>
    For clubs joining the pilot programme, current commercial terms include a <strong>free first
    trial month, with no commitment</strong>, before any payment. The rates set out below take
    effect at the end of this trial period if the club wishes to continue.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Purpose and scope</h2>
  <p>
    These Sales Terms (hereinafter the <strong>"Terms"</strong>) govern the supply of the Scluba
    service to golf clubs, public courses, driving range operators and equivalent structures
    (hereinafter the <strong>"Customer"</strong>) by Scluba (hereinafter the <strong>"Provider"</strong>),
    whose details are set out in the <a href="/en/legal/legal-notice/">legal notice</a>.
  </p>
  <p>
    The service is a SaaS (Software as a Service) software allowing the creation and distribution
    of a digital scorecard branded with the Customer's identity, accessible to players via a QR
    code (hereinafter the <strong>"Service"</strong>).
  </p>
  <p>
    Any order placed by the Customer implies unconditional acceptance of these Terms, to the
    exclusion of any other document, in particular the Customer's general purchasing terms.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Description of the Service</h2>
  <p>The Service includes, depending on the plan subscribed to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>the <strong>design and delivery</strong> of a recap card page branded with the Customer's identity (logo, colors, photos), within 24 working hours after brief validation;</li>
    <li><strong>hosting</strong> and maintenance of this page on the Provider's infrastructure;</li>
    <li>provision of a <strong>physical QR frame</strong> to be placed at the Customer's reception counter;</li>
    <li>access, for players scanning the QR code, to the <strong>Scluba web app</strong> (no install) and, depending on the plan, to the Scluba iOS and Android mobile applications;</li>
    <li>delivery of a <strong>monthly report</strong> by email to the Customer (scans, rounds played, social shares);</li>
    <li>user support by email during business hours.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Plans and pricing</h2>
  <p>
    The Service is offered under two subscription plans, excluding taxes:
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Plan</th><th>Monthly price</th><th>3-year commitment price</th><th>Scope</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Essential</td>
        <td>€49 ex-VAT / month</td>
        <td>€39 ex-VAT / month (−20%)</td>
        <td>Branded recap card + QR frame + reporting</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Complete</td>
        <td>€79 ex-VAT / month</td>
        <td>€63 ex-VAT / month (−20%)</td>
        <td>Essential + iOS/Android apps + GPS tracking + player accounts</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>
    Prices are exclusive of taxes; applicable VAT is added according to the relevant tax regime.
    The Provider reserves the right to amend its pricing; any change is notified to the Customer
    by email with 60 days' notice and applies only at the end of the current period.
  </p>
  <p>
    The Provider may occasionally offer promotional terms ("first month free", launch discount,
    partnership). Such offers are governed by their own conditions and create no acquired right
    for subsequent renewals.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Order and effective date</h2>
  <p>
    Orders are formalized by signature of a purchase order, an accepted quotation, or by explicit
    validation by email referring to these Terms. The effective date is the date of validation by
    the Customer.
  </p>
  <p>
    Unless otherwise stated, the mockup is delivered within 24 working hours after receipt of the
    necessary materials (Customer site URL, logo, content access). The physical QR frame is
    shipped within 7 working days of mockup validation.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Trial period</h2>
  <p>
    Save as otherwise contractually agreed, the Provider may grant the Customer a <strong>free
    trial period</strong>, the duration of which is specified at order (default: 1 month). The
    trial period does not commit the Customer to continuing the engagement.
  </p>
  <p>
    At the end of the trial period, in the absence of notification of termination by the Customer
    at least 7 days before its end, the subscription enters into force at the rates of the chosen
    plan.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Payment terms</h2>
  <p>
    Payment is made by SEPA direct debit, bank transfer, or credit card via the payment provider
    N/A — free pilot, no payments collected.
  </p>
  <p>
    Monthly subscriptions are invoiced monthly in advance. Subscriptions with a 3-year commitment
    are invoiced monthly or annually depending on the order, and the commitment covers the full
    duration.
  </p>
  <p>
    Any invoice is due 30 days end of month. Late payment automatically gives rise, without prior
    notice, to late-payment penalties at the European Central Bank's most recent refinancing
    operation rate plus 10 points (French Commercial Code article L.441-10), as well as a
    standard recovery fee of €40 (article D.441-5).
  </p>

  <h2>7. Term and termination</h2>
  <h3>7.1 Subscription without commitment</h3>
  <p>
    The monthly subscription is concluded for one month, tacitly renewed. The Customer can
    terminate at any time by email to <a href="mailto:team@scluba.com">team@scluba.com</a>,
    effective at the end of the current monthly period. No prorata refund is owed.
  </p>

  <h3>7.2 Subscription with 3-year commitment</h3>
  <p>
    The committed subscription is concluded for a firm term of 36 months, tacitly renewed for
    annual periods. The Customer may terminate at the end of each period with 60 days' notice.
    Any early termination during the firm period renders the balance of remaining monthly
    payments due.
  </p>

  <h3>7.3 Termination for breach</h3>
  <p>
    In the event of a serious breach by either party of its obligations, the other party may
    terminate the contract by operation of law, after a formal notice that has remained without
    effect for 30 days, without prejudice to any damages it may claim.
  </p>

  <h3>7.4 Consequences of termination</h3>
  <p>
    Termination entails the immediate cessation of access to the Service. The Customer may
    request, within 30 days following termination, an export of the data collected via the
    Service in CSV or JSON format. Beyond that, data is erased under the conditions of the
    <a href="/en/legal/privacy/">Privacy policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Service level (SLA)</h2>
  <p>
    The Provider undertakes to use reasonable means to ensure Service availability of <strong>99%
    on a monthly average</strong>, excluding scheduled maintenance and force majeure.
  </p>
  <p>
    Scheduled maintenance windows are carried out preferably at night (Paris time) and notified by
    email at least 48 hours in advance when likely to impact the Service.
  </p>
  <p>
    In the event of uninterrupted unavailability exceeding 24 consecutive hours attributable to
    the Provider, the Customer may request a credit equivalent to one day of subscription per 24
    hours of unavailability, capped at one month's subscription per calendar month.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Provider obligations</h2>
  <p>The Provider undertakes to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>provide the Service professionally and in accordance with the description above;</li>
    <li>host data under secure conditions;</li>
    <li>comply with GDPR obligations and sign a data processing agreement with the Customer where required;</li>
    <li>notify the Customer without delay of any data breach affecting its data;</li>
    <li>provide user support by email during business hours.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>10. Customer obligations</h2>
  <p>The Customer undertakes to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>provide the Provider with the materials necessary for delivery (logo, brand guidelines, photos, website access);</li>
    <li>warrant that it holds the necessary rights over the materials provided (in particular trademarks and photographs);</li>
    <li>not use the Service for unlawful purposes;</li>
    <li>relay to its players the information useful for using the Service;</li>
    <li>pay invoices on the agreed deadlines;</li>
    <li>inform the Provider of any technical incident or fraudulent use observed.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>11. Intellectual property</h2>
  <p>
    The Provider retains all rights over the Service, its source code, interface, documentation
    and any improvements it may make. No assignment of intellectual property rights is made to
    the Customer under these Terms.
  </p>
  <p>
    The Customer retains all rights over its trademark, logo, visual identity and content. It
    grants the Provider, for the duration of the contract and solely for the purposes of
    performing the Service, a non-exclusive right to use these elements on the branded page and
    the recap card distributed to players.
  </p>
  <p>
    The Provider may, unless the Customer objects in writing, cite the Customer's name and logo
    as a commercial reference (case study, "trusted by" page).
  </p>

  <h2>12. Personal data</h2>
  <p>
    In the performance of the Service, the Provider acts as a <strong>processor</strong> within
    the meaning of article 28 GDPR for personal data of players processed on behalf of the
    Customer. A data processing agreement (DPA) may be concluded at the Customer's request.
  </p>
  <p>
    For data collected directly by the Provider (site visitors, optional player accounts), the
    Provider acts as <strong>controller</strong>, in accordance with the
    <a href="/en/legal/privacy/">Privacy policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>13. Confidentiality</h2>
  <p>
    Each party undertakes to keep strictly confidential the technical, commercial, financial or
    strategic information received from the other under the contract, and to use it only for the
    purposes of its performance. This obligation lasts for 3 years after the end of the contract.
  </p>

  <h2>14. Liability</h2>
  <p>
    The Provider has a best-efforts obligation in performing the Service. Its liability can only
    be engaged in case of proven fault and for direct and foreseeable damages.
  </p>
  <p>
    In any case, the Provider's total liability under the contract, all causes combined, is
    limited to an amount equivalent to the sums actually paid by the Customer over the 12 months
    preceding the triggering event.
  </p>
  <p>
    All indirect damages are excluded, in particular loss of revenue, loss of customers, damage
    to reputation, loss of opportunity, loss of data.
  </p>

  <h2>15. Insurance</h2>
  <p>
    The Provider declares that it is insured under its professional civil liability with a
    notoriously solvent company, for amounts covering the financial consequences of its
    liability.
  </p>

  <h2>16. Force majeure</h2>
  <p>
    Neither party shall be held liable for non-performance of its obligations to the extent that
    such non-performance is caused by a force majeure event as defined by article 1218 of the
    French Civil Code and French case law.
  </p>

  <h2>17. Subcontracting and assignment</h2>
  <p>
    The Provider may use subcontractors for the supply of the Service, subject to assuming full
    responsibility for them towards the Customer.
  </p>
  <p>
    The contract may not be assigned by either party without the prior written agreement of the
    other, except for an assignment within an internal restructuring or a global business
    transfer, subject to prior information.
  </p>

  <h2>18. Amendments</h2>
  <p>
    The Provider may amend these Terms. Any substantial amendment is notified to the Customer
    by email at least 60 days before its entry into force, and is enforceable against the
    Customer only at the end of the current contractual period, unless expressly accepted in
    advance.
  </p>

  <h2>19. Governing law and jurisdiction</h2>
  <p>
    These Terms are governed by French law. Failing amicable agreement, any dispute relating to
    their interpretation or performance shall be submitted to the exclusive jurisdiction of the
    courts within the jurisdiction of the Provider's registered office, including in case of
    multiple defendants or third-party claims.
  </p>

  <h2>20. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For any questions about these Terms: <a href="mailto:team@scluba.com">team@scluba.com</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
